 The Mooikloof Equestrian Estate on the outskirts of Pretoria East has become one of the most sought-after residential addresses among the Jacaranda city’s well-heeled. This palatial home boasts seven bedroom suites, including a master suite with its own lounge and study, five living areas, a games room, air-conditioning and underfloor heating, six fully equipped stables, a park-like garden with a borehole and full irrigation.  This historical, beautifully restored Sir Herbert Baker homestead was designed circa 1898 and offers six bedrooms and four bathrooms. Generous proportions extend throughout, with sea views over the yacht basin and the picturesque village of Simon’s Town below. The house has large living areas and a country kitchen complete with a butler’s pantry. A separate caretaker’s cottage with single garage is set under the trees in the garden.